austin-tx.name: Austin
austin-tx.weather: Austin is characterized by hot summers and mild winters.  Average high temperatures surpass 90 degrees on 109 days per year, and winters are dry and temperate.

baltimore-md.name: Baltimore
baltimore-md.weather: Baltimore has four distinct seasons.  Summers are hot and humid, and it can occasionally snow in the winter.

boston-ma.name: Boston
boston-ma.weather: Boston has four seasons, ranging from a hot and humid summer to an icy, snowy winter.  New England fall is known for its temperate weather and colorful beauty, as the deciduous trees shed their bright leaves.

charlotte-nc.name: Charlotte
charlotte-nc.weather: Charlotte has four distinct seasons.  Winters are cool, with an average high of 42 degrees Fahrenheit in January.  Summers are hot, with an average high of 90 degrees in July.

chicago-il.name: Chicago
chicago-il.weather: Although the nickname Windy City refers to loud-mouthed politicians

columbus-oh.name: Columbus
columbus-oh.weather: Columbus has cold winters and hot, humid summers.  While the winters are not particularly snowy, winter temperatures are usually in the eh 20s and 30s.  The average high in July is 85 degrees Fahrenheit.

dallas-tx.name: Dallas
dallas-tx.weather: Dallas is very hot, with temperatures often over 100 degrees Fahrenheit in the summer and temperatures ranging from 30 to 70 degrees in the winter.

denver-co.name: Denver
denver-co.weather: Denver is very sunny, with an average of 300 sunny days per year.  The city has four distinct seasons, and average highs range from 90 degrees in July to 44 degrees Fahrenheit in December.

detroit-mi.name: Detroit
detroit-mi.weather: Detroit winters are cold and snowy, with an average temperature of 27 degrees Fahrenheit in January.  Summers are hot, sometimes reaching 90 degrees.

honolulu-hi.name: Honolulu
honolulu-hi.weather: Honolulu is famous for its beautiful weather, with long sunny days that can be spent on the beach.  The temperature varies little throughout the year, and average highs are 80-90 degrees Fahrenheit.

houston-tx.name: Houston
houston-tx.weather: Houston is characterized by mild winters and hot summers with temperatures regularly exceeding 90 degrees Fahrenheit.  Although the occasional tornado may pass nearby, Houston is not a part of the \\Tornado Alley\\that contains much of Texas.\\\\"\"\\\"\"\"\"\""

indianapolis-in.name: Indianapolis
indianapolis-in.weather: Indianapolis has four distinct seasons, with a hot, humid summer (temperatures often exceed 90 degrees) and cold winters (with temperatures in the 30s).

jacksonville-fl.name: Jacksonville
jacksonville-fl.weather: Jacksonville has mild winters and hot, humid summers.  Highs range from 64 to 92 degrees year-round.

los-angeles-long-beach-ca.name: Los Angeles-Long Beach
los-angeles-long-beach-ca.weather: Sunny Los Angeles is always bright and warm, with an average temperature of 75 degrees in the afternoon and 57 degrees at night.  The desert climate is very dry, and it rarely rains.

memphis-tn.name: Memphis
memphis-tn.weather: Memphis has four distinct seasons, with very hot, humid summers and mild winters.  July has an average high of 92 degrees Fahrenheit, and January has an average high of 50 degrees Fahrenheit.

new-york-manhattan-ny.name: New York (Manhattan)
new-york-manhattan-ny.weather: New York City has four distinct seasons.  Summers are hot and humid, winters are icy and cold, springs are rainy, and the New England fall is gorgeous when Central Park becomes littered with brightly colored leaves.

philadelphia-pa.name: Philadelphia
philadelphia-pa.weather: Philadelphia is characterized by cold winters and hot, humid summers.  The average temperature falls as low as 32 degrees Fahrenheit in January, but they rise to 76 degrees in July.

phoenix-az.name: Phoenix
phoenix-az.weather: Phoenix has extremely hot summers and warm winters, with temperatures exceeding 100 degrees Fahrenheit for an average of 110 days per year.

san-diego-ca.name: San Diego
san-diego-ca.weather: San Diego has warm, dry summers and warm winters. The climate is temperate, with a January average low of 50 degrees Fahrenheit and an August average high of 78 degrees Fahrenheit.  It has been rated as one of the top 10 best climates in the Farmer's Almanac.

san-francisco-ca.name: San Francisco
san-francisco-ca.weather: San Francisco is temperate, generally cool and foggy in the morning and sunny in the afternoon with a temperature consistently between 55 and 70 degrees Fahrenheit all year round.  Due to the city's microclimates, it can be sunny and warm in one neighborhood and foggy and cold a mile away.

seattle-wa.name: Seattle
seattle-wa.weather: Seattle has a temperate climate, with mild winters and warm summers.  Seattle winters are very rainy, but the summers are dry.

washington-arlington-alexandria-dc-va.name: Washington-Arlington-Alexandria
washington-arlington-alexandria-dc-va.weather: Washington D.C. has hot, humid summers (with an average temperature of 79 degrees Fahrenheit) and chilly winters (with an average temperature of 38 degrees).  The city is susceptible to the occasional nor'easter blizzard, and there are often thunderstorms in the summer.
